## Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // ~√(1/2)

// Simulation configuration
const config = {
  gravity: 4000,             // Repulsion strength between nodes
  stiffion: 0.004,           // Spring stiffness (default)
  dampingFriction: 0.92,     // Velocity damping per tick
  centering: 0.0003,         // Centering force strength
  particleRate: 40,          // Max number of particles
  particleSpeed: 0.04,       // Particle speed decay factor
  deltaTime: 0.06            // Smoothing interpolation speed
};

// --- NODES ---
const nodes = [
  { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "zeta",    label: "Zeta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// --- EDGES (springs) ---
const edges = [
  { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "zeta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: "beta",  b: "zeta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "beta",  b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// --- CAMERA ---
let camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// --- PARTICLES ---
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// Physics: apply forces
function applyForces() {
  // 1) Node-node repulsion (like charges repelling)
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      let force = config.gravity / (dist * dist);
      let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      let fy = (dy / dist) * force;
      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2) Spring forces along edges
  for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
    let nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
    let nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
    let dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    let dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    let displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
    let force = (edges[i].k || config.stiffion) * displacement;
    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3) Damping + centering + position integration
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centering;  // center pull X
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centering;  // center pull Y
    nodes[i].vx *= config.dampingFriction;
    nodes[i].vy *= config.dampingFriction;
    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}

// Spawn a particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.particleRate) return;
  let node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  let angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;
  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2
  });
}

// Update particles (move, age, remove dead)
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    let p = particles[i];
    p.vx *= 1 - config.particleSpeed * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.particleSpeed * 0.125;
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}

// Smooth camera follow
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.deltaTime;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.deltaTime;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.deltaTime;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
  applyForces();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60fps
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** — the physics engine behind a network/node visualization (like D3.js force layouts). Specifically:

### 🔵 Nodes (6 total)
Six named nodes (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Zeta, Epsilon) with varying radii representing importance/size.

### 🔗 Edges (8 springs)
Spring connections between nodes with rest lengths and stiffness values. Alpha is the central hub connected to all others.

### ⚡ Physics Engine
1. **Repulsion** — All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, like electric charges) to prevent overlap
2. **Spring attraction** — Connected nodes are pulled toward their rest distance via Hooke's law
3. **Centering force** — Weak gravity pulls all nodes toward (400, 300)
4. **Velocity damping** — 0.92× friction per frame prevents runaway oscillation

### ✨ Particles
Decorative particles spawn from random nodes every 3 frames, drift outward slowly, and die after 800–2000 frames — creating a subtle ambient "energy" effect.

### 🎥 Camera
Smooth camera interpolation follows a target position with easing.

### ⏱️ Main Loop
Runs at ~60fps via `setInterval(tick, 16)`.

> **In summary**: This is the **headless physics simulation** for an animated, interactive network graph visualization. It computes positions but contains no rendering code — that would be in a separate draw/render function.
